OL,3,CFormer police sergeant who ran
OL,4,Cfraudulent betting syndicate jailed
OL,6,FThe 68-year-old from Chatham ran an
OL,7,Felaborate Ponzi scheme whereby he
OL,8,Fconvinced more than 6,000 gamblers
OL,9,Fthat his formula for betting on the
OL,10,Foutcome of horse races would result in
OL,11,Fa higher percentage of positive
OL,12,Foutcomes.
OL,14,FHis Layezy Racing syndicate was
OL,15,Ffailing, but Stanley continued to
OL,16,Ffalsely report that the scheme had
OL,17,Fmade a profit.
OL,19,FWatch: Police arrest Stanley at his
OL,20,Fhome in Kent.
